  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project is increasing engagement and participation in political process in Zambia, through provision of strengthened media platforms for accountability and public dialogue. The project is particularly targeting women and rural audiences under-represented in political processes and underserved by mainstream media. In June 2016, an additional &#xA3;49,950 was granted to support MUVI TV to deliver TV election debates. In November 2016, the project was expanded to include a radio drama addressing social norms and an endline quant survey.</narrative>
